<body>
    <h1>Department of Library and Information Science</h1>

    <h2>Vision</h2>
    <p>To be a leader in the field of library and information science education, producing knowledgeable and skilled professionals who will effectively meet the needs of the information society.</p>

    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>Our mission is to prepare students to become innovative and effective leaders in libraries and information centers, committed to fostering access to information, promoting literacy, and ensuring the availability of resources to diverse communities.</p>

    <h2>Goals</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide a comprehensive and rigorous curriculum.</li>
        <li>Encourage research and scholarship among faculty and students.</li>
        <li>Prepare graduates for successful careers in various information professions.</li>
        <li>Advance the profession through service and community involvement.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Stakeholders</h2>
    <p>Our stakeholders include students, faculty, alumni, library and information professionals, and the community served by our graduates.</p>

    <h2>LIS Program Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>To foster critical thinking and problem-solving skills in information contexts.</li>
        <li>To develop an understanding of the social, cultural, and technological impacts of information.</li>
        <li>To equip students with the skills necessary to manage, organize, and retrieve information effectively.</li>
        <li>To promote collaboration and effective communication within and across professional boundaries.</li>
    </ul>
</body>
